<subSubSection id="C35A04916C41AD75FF1EBEAFBB178BB2" pageId="1" pageNumber="582" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BFF571A6C41AD75FF1EBEAFBB178BB2" blockId="1.[151,1436,151,1059]" pageId="1" pageNumber="582">
<emphasis id="B9348B086C41AD75FF1EBEAFBB0B8B97" bold="true" box="[151,279,186,209]" pageId="1" pageNumber="582">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name is from the Latin for “two spotted” and refers to the two brownish pigmented spots on each wing.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C35A04916C41AD75FF4EBF15BACF8A8A" pageId="1" pageNumber="582" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BFF571A6C41AD75FF4EBF15BACF8A8A" blockId="1.[151,1436,151,1059]" pageId="1" pageNumber="582">
<emphasis id="B9348B086C41AD75FF4EBF15BB288A51" bold="true" box="[199,308,256,279]" pageId="1" pageNumber="582">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C402C996C41AD75FDFDBF15B9388A51" box="[628,804,255,279]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="582" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="conglomerata">
<emphasis id="B9348B086C41AD75FDFDBF15B8968A51" box="[628,650,256,279]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="582">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B9348B086C41AD75FD11BEEAB9388A51" box="[664,804,255,279]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="582">conglomerata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in terms of two wing-spots. It can be distinguished from the latter in: (
<number id="3D88453D6C41AD75FF70BF37BB1F8A7F" box="[249,259,290,313]" pageId="1" pageNumber="582" value="1.0">1</number>
) Costa long (costal index about 
<number id="3D88453D6C41AD75FDC1BF37B86B8A7F" box="[584,631,290,313]" pageId="1" pageNumber="582" value="0.61">0.61</number>
), and the latter Costa shorter (costal index about 
<number id="3D88453D6C41AD75FBD7BF37BEDA8A7F" box="[1118,1222,290,313]" pageId="1" pageNumber="582" value="0.435" valueMax="0.44" valueMin="0.43">0.43–0.44</number>
). (
<number id="3D88453D6C41AD75FB57BF37BEF08A7F" box="[1246,1260,290,313]" pageId="1" pageNumber="582" value="2.0">2</number>
) wing with a big, diamond, brownish pigmented spot between the apex of vein R 
<number id="3D88453D6C41AD75FC9DBF41B9078A26" box="[788,795,340,352]" pageId="1" pageNumber="582" value="4.0">4</number>
+ 
<number id="3D88453D6C41AD75FCAABF41B9358A26" box="[803,809,340,352]" pageId="1" pageNumber="582" value="5.0">5</number>
and the middle of vein M 
<number id="3D88453D6C41AD75FBA6BF41BE2A8A26" box="[1071,1078,340,352]" pageId="1" pageNumber="582" value="1.0">1</number>
, and the spot is inclined 
<number id="3D88453D6C41AD75FAA6BF50BF558A1A" box="[1327,1353,325,348]" pageId="1" pageNumber="582" value="45.0">45</number>
degrees with costa; and a small wedge-shape brown pigmented spot between the middle of veins M 
<number id="3D88453D6C41AD75FBA3BF6FBE2D8AC0" box="[1066,1073,378,390]" pageId="1" pageNumber="582" value="1.0">1</number>
and M 
<number id="3D88453D6C41AD75FBFFBF6FBE618AC0" box="[1142,1149,378,390]" pageId="1" pageNumber="582" value="2.0">2</number>
. And in the latter, wing with an oblong brownish spot on anterior margin above apex of M 
<number id="3D88453D6C41AD75FC9BBF8AB9058AED" box="[786,793,415,427]" pageId="1" pageNumber="582" value="1.0">1</number>
vein, and a rounded brown patch between apex of M 
<number id="3D88453D6C41AD75FACABF8ABF568AED" box="[1347,1354,415,427]" pageId="1" pageNumber="582" value="1.0">1</number>
and M 
<number id="3D88453D6C41AD75FA1CBF8ABF808AED" box="[1429,1436,415,427]" pageId="1" pageNumber="582" value="2.0">2</number>
veins.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C35A04916C41AD77FF4EBFCDBB928A7F" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="584" pageId="1" pageNumber="582" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BFF571A6C41AD75FF4EBFCDB9028AA9" blockId="1.[151,1436,151,1059]" box="[199,798,472,495]" pageId="1" pageNumber="582">
<emphasis id="B9348B086C41AD75FF4EBFCDBB4E8AA9" bold="true" box="[199,338,472,495]" pageId="1" pageNumber="582">Description.</emphasis>
Male. Body length 
<number id="3D88453D6C41AD75FDAFBFCDB8598AA9" box="[550,581,472,495]" pageId="1" pageNumber="582" value="1.9">1.9</number>
–2.0 mm (
<figureCitation id="137B4B9F6C41AD75FD3ABFCDB9128AA9" box="[691,782,472,495]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,244,2017,2038]" captionTargetBox="[214,1372,1111,1992]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[214,1372,1111,1992]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Megaselia bisticta sp. nov. body in left lateral view. Scale bar = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/265661/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="582">
Figure 
<number id="3D88453D6C41AD75FC88BFCDB9128AA9" box="[769,782,472,495]" pageId="1" pageNumber="582" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFF571A6C41AD75FF4EBFEFB9B889F9" blockId="1.[151,1436,151,1059]" pageId="1" pageNumber="582">
Head (
<figureCitation id="137B4B9F6C41AD75FE86BFEFBB728957" box="[271,366,506,529]" captionStart="FIGURES 2 – 10" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1906,1927]" captionTargetBox="[168,1426,211,1867]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,194,1882]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 2 – 10. Megaselia bisticta sp. nov. 2: head; 3: fore leg; 4: mid leg; 5: hind leg; 6: wing; 7, 9: hypopygium in left lateral view; 8, 10: hypopygium in right lateral view. 3 – 6: Scale bars = 0.2 mm; 2, 7 – 10: Scale bars = 0.05 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/265662/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="582">
Figure 
<number id="3D88453D6C41AD75FED7BFEFBB728957" box="[350,366,506,529]" pageId="1" pageNumber="582" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
). Frons black, width about 
<quantity id="4CB8FAFF6C41AD75FD13BFEFB8EC8957" box="[666,752,506,529]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="582" unit="mm" value="0.3">0.3 mm</quantity>
, broader than height (2.0: 
<number id="3D88453D6C41AD75FB86BFEFBE058957" box="[1039,1049,506,529]" pageId="1" pageNumber="582" value="1.0">1</number>
), with about 
<number id="3D88453D6C41AD75FB23BFEFBED98957" box="[1194,1221,506,529]" pageId="1" pageNumber="582" value="50.0">50</number>
hairs and a distinct median furrow. Lower supra-antennal bristles short, about 
<number id="3D88453D6C41AD75FC9EBC08B9388972" box="[791,804,541,564]" pageId="1" pageNumber="582" value="2.0">2</number>
/ 
<number id="3D88453D6C41AD75FCA4BC08B9258972" box="[813,825,541,564]" pageId="1" pageNumber="582" value="3.0">3</number>
as long as upper pair. Pre-ocellars slightly further from each other than upper supra-antennals. Antials closer to antero-laterals than to upper supra-antennal bristles and slightly lower than antero-laterals. Pre-ocellars nearly parallel on frons to medio-laterals and with equal distance each other. Postpedicels black or dark brown and without SPS vesicles. Arista obviously longer than frons width. Palps yellow with strong bristles which are obviously longer than maximum width of palps.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFF571A6C41AD75FF4EBCDFBF758F59" blockId="1.[151,1436,151,1059]" pageId="1" pageNumber="582">
Thorax. Thoracic dorsum black and flank dark brown. Mesopleuron with a few fine hairs. Notopleuron with 
<number id="3D88453D6C41AD75FA07BCDFBF8789A7" box="[1422,1435,714,737]" pageId="1" pageNumber="582" value="3.0">3</number>
bristles and no cleft. Scutellum with a pair of bristles. Legs (
<figureCitation id="137B4B9F6C41AD75FCC4BCF8B9CF8842" box="[845,979,749,772]" captionStart="FIGURES 2 – 10" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1906,1927]" captionTargetBox="[168,1426,211,1867]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,194,1882]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 2 – 10. Megaselia bisticta sp. nov. 2: head; 3: fore leg; 4: mid leg; 5: hind leg; 6: wing; 7, 9: hypopygium in left lateral view; 8, 10: hypopygium in right lateral view. 3 – 6: Scale bars = 0.2 mm; 2, 7 – 10: Scale bars = 0.05 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/265662/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="582">
Figures 
<number id="3D88453D6C41AD75FC23BCF8B9CF8842" box="[938,979,749,772]" pageId="1" pageNumber="582" value="4.0" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="3.0">3–5</number>
</figureCitation>
) brown, but fore legs paler. 
<collectingCountry id="F357178A6C41AD75FA92BCF8BF4C8842" box="[1307,1360,749,772]" name="India" pageId="1" pageNumber="582">Hind</collectingCountry>
femur darkened at tip. Fore metatarsus longer than joints 
<number id="3D88453D6C41AD75FD31BD05B8DB8861" box="[696,711,784,807]" pageId="1" pageNumber="582" value="2.0">2</number>
+ 
<number id="3D88453D6C41AD75FD51BD05B8F98861" box="[728,741,784,807]" pageId="1" pageNumber="582" value="3.0">3</number>
. Dorsal hair palisade of mid tibia extends 
<number id="3D88453D6C41AD75FB22BD05BED08861" box="[1195,1228,784,807]" pageId="1" pageNumber="582" value="0.6">0.6</number>
of its length. Hairs short below basal half of hind femur and anteroventral row of outer half, but the latter is longer than the former. 
<collectingCountry id="F357178A6C41AD75FAEFBD27BF87880F" box="[1382,1435,818,841]" name="India" pageId="1" pageNumber="582">Hind</collectingCountry>
tibia with strong posterodorsal hairs and without anterodorsal hairs. Wings (
<figureCitation id="137B4B9F6C41AD75FC57BD40BE22882A" box="[990,1086,853,876]" captionStart="FIGURES 2 – 10" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1906,1927]" captionTargetBox="[168,1426,211,1867]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,194,1882]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 2 – 10. Megaselia bisticta sp. nov. 2: head; 3: fore leg; 4: mid leg; 5: hind leg; 6: wing; 7, 9: hypopygium in left lateral view; 8, 10: hypopygium in right lateral view. 3 – 6: Scale bars = 0.2 mm; 2, 7 – 10: Scale bars = 0.05 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/265662/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="582">
Figure 
<number id="3D88453D6C41AD75FBB9BD40BE22882A" box="[1072,1086,853,876]" pageId="1" pageNumber="582" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
) nearly hyaline, with yellowish brown veins. A big diamond brownish pigmented spot is between the apex of vein R 
<number id="3D88453D6C41AD75FBA4BD92BE2988D5" box="[1069,1077,903,915]" pageId="1" pageNumber="582" value="4.0">4</number>
+ 
<number id="3D88453D6C41AD75FBB4BD92BE5888D5" box="[1085,1092,903,915]" pageId="1" pageNumber="582" value="5.0">5</number>
and the middle of vein M 
<number id="3D88453D6C41AD75FAE9BD92BF7B88D5" box="[1376,1383,903,915]" pageId="1" pageNumber="582" value="1.0">1</number>
, and the spot is inclined 
<number id="3D88453D6C41AD75FEEDBD88BB6388F2" box="[356,383,925,948]" pageId="1" pageNumber="582" value="45.0">45</number>
degrees with costa; and a small wedge-shape brown pigmented spot is between the middle of veins M 
<number id="3D88453D6C41AD75FF27BDDABAA9889D" box="[174,181,975,987]" pageId="1" pageNumber="582" value="1.0">1</number>
and M 
<number id="3D88453D6C41AD75FE8FBDDABB11889D" box="[262,269,975,987]" pageId="1" pageNumber="582" value="2.0">2</number>
. The area between the spots and the anterior margin of the wings is pale brown. Costal index about 
<number id="3D88453D6C41AD75FAEFBDD5BF848891" box="[1382,1432,960,983]" pageId="1" pageNumber="582" value="0.61">0.61</number>
. Costal ratio 
<number id="3D88453D6C41AD75FE96BDF0BB5B88BA" box="[287,327,997,1020]" pageId="1" pageNumber="582" value="2.6">2.6</number>
: 
<number id="3D88453D6C41AD75FEC2BDF0BB6F88BA" box="[331,371,997,1020]" pageId="1" pageNumber="582" value="2.6">2.6</number>
: 
<number id="3D88453D6C41AD75FEFEBDF0BB9D88BA" box="[375,385,997,1020]" pageId="1" pageNumber="582" value="1.0">1</number>
. Costal cilia about 
<quantity id="4CB8FAFF6C41AD75FDD0BDF0B8A988BA" box="[601,693,997,1020]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7" pageId="1" pageNumber="582" unit="mm" value="0.07">0.07mm</quantity>
. Vein Sc runs to R 
<number id="3D88453D6C41AD75FC07BDF0B98488BA" box="[910,920,997,1020]" pageId="1" pageNumber="582" value="1.0">1</number>
. Base of vein Rs with 
<number id="3D88453D6C41AD75FB12BDF0BEB488BA" box="[1179,1192,997,1020]" pageId="1" pageNumber="582" value="1.0">1</number>
minute hair, which is slightly shorter than vein R 
<number id="3D88453D6C41AD75FE30BA02BBDD8F65" box="[441,449,1047,1059]" pageId="1" pageNumber="582" value="2.0">2</number>
+ 
<number id="3D88453D6C41AD75FE40BA02BBCC8F65" box="[457,464,1047,1059]" pageId="1" pageNumber="582" value="3.0">3</number>
. Vein M 
